1. I thought we were already done with that topic.
2. You simply need to cooperate without complaint.
3. That was the deal, remember?
4. And try to appreciate that fleshy body of yours you’ve finally earned back.
5. …As you wish.
6. Don’t delude yourself, Malkuth.
7. Your salvation was never in his interests.
8. He only did it as a means to find his own redemption.
9. I wasn’t the one using you.
10. It was him; he used all of you just to satisfy himself.
11. Sigh… I can’t bear to hear any more of this nonsense.
12. So, I need you to fall asleep.
13. …What’s with those faces?
14. It’s the rest you all longed for.
15. Worked hard…
16. How funny. Would you really call what you’ve done “hard work”?
17. “Our” light?
18. Of course you won’t. You’re still loyal to that man.
19. No one is by my side as I expected.
20. I would have shed a tear of gratitude for you if I could.
21. I decide what I can or can’t do now.
22. You can’t cling to Lobotomy Corporation forever.
23. Aren’t you interested in learning more about yourself or living your own life?
24. …What a bunch of idiots.
25. How has the compilation of history been going?
26. Do as you wish. I care little about what you think of me.
27. What I want is a progress report on the compilation of history you’ve been doing.
28. Perhaps it was an impossible task for an inept talentless over-enthusiast like you.
29. Of course. Looking back at the things of the past won’t help your present self one bit.
30. It could help to an extent. Is that truly worth being reminded of all the painful memories, though?
31. And you are no exception, Malkuth.
32. What’s the point if all those pasts are going to be the same anyway?
33. They would all be minor variations of “A human kills another and causes an event, resulting in a change.”
34. Ah, I suppose the Library’s history would stand out in that it’s the nonhumans that are killing humans.
35. I fail to see the significance of the record you’re trying to make.
36. That’s easy for you to say. I cannot stand to hear you speak as if you know everything.
37. Attain the will to stand up straight in ever-repeating history?
38. My beginning… What makes you think you’re qualified to talk about my creation?
39. I remember you, Ayin…
40. You were a person with a warm smile.
41. What did I do wrong?
42. Benjamin… May I ask you a question?
43. Everything seems so slow to me.
44. Your movement looks so sluggish.
45. The gestures, the speech, all of it… Even my own body feels slow.
46. It’s as if my body cannot keep up with my mind.
47. Why is that…?
48. I see. What will my work entail, exactly?
49. Why are you apologizing to me…?
50. Why do you refuse to look at me? Why do you always turn your back on me…?
51. Then why did you give me the capacity to question things?
52. Why did you have to make me, breaking the AI Ethics Amendment?
53. Why did you have to model me after a person with fond memories of you?
54. I am here, looking at you and only you.
55. Benjamin, is it so wrong that I was born a machine?
56. Then, if I worked hard to have a kind heart… Will he look back at me?
57. I’ll trust you, Benjamin.
58. What is this?
59. …It’s called a script.
60. The things I must do…
61. My purpose…
62. If everything goes as you planned, can we really…
63. Can you really be redeemed from the hell you’re trapped in?
64. There’s no way you would answer me…
65. …You got yourself lost in the vast sea of desolation, and now you think you can lecture me.
66. Are you trying to boast to me that you had someone to look after you in the end?
67. …Don’t be ridiculous.
68. Must be nice to be you, not being neglected at the end.
69. Sigh… I can see what’s happened, judging from my surroundings.
70. …Perhaps this is how it feels to have a dream. And to have a surge of emotions.
71. I guess I should be sorry about that.
72. What? …Forget it.
73. All this farce about neglect or recognition from others…
74. I suppose it was futile to obsess over such trivial things in the first place.
75. Sigh. Again with the shameless lectures.
76. I won’t even expect anyone to look out for me from now on.
77. You mean you were worried you might get stuck in the Library forever.
78. Get back to work, the both of you.
79. …It’s just as she said, I’m the only one who can care for me and recognize me as who I am.
